caption: Miss the prospect. Great food fun staff great place. Always quality

I really enjoyed this place. It is very spacious and cozy. We were greeted and seated as soon as we walked in. Our server was very attentive. They have one of the best mac and cheeses in Park Slope but I highly recommend eating it there, it does not taste as good in a take out container. The buffalo wings and chips with charred tomato salsa and guacamole were both delicious as well. I had the steak with mashed potatoes and the steak could have used more salt and seasoning, the fat could have been trimmed off better as well, next time I go I will opt for the burger and fries which looked delicious.
Yummy brunch, great friendly staff! Would go here every week if it wasn’t so far from the heights
Drinks were lit! Food was so delicious! Ambience was great!
I go here for brunch every time I'm in the area. Everything is delicious and the servers are super nice.
Good food and drinks, felt the whole place was a little too dark for my liking.
Nice bar. Our server was attentive. Pub food was good. I would go back if I was in the neighborhood.
Had a group dinner here. Great food, drinks, and service!
Food is great. The booze even greater
Excellent happy hour and delicious food!

I’ve loved this place since it opened a few years ago. I mostly come for the food, but the bar area looks great - spacious and clean and the right balance of casual and classy. The food is what keeps me coming back. The brunch is great - love the French toast. Dinner food is several steps above standard pub food. My wife loves the roast chicken, and I’ve enjoyed their burger. The fries are quite good as well. Their chicken finger appetizers with the sweet chili sauce are definitely kryptonite for my waistline too. Portions are great and I usually end up taking some home. Wait staff is good - sometimes they have a lot of tables on what seemed like a quieter night, but if you’re not in too much of a rush it’s really no big deal.
Great food and super friendly service
The food in this place is amazing, customer service is the best !!!!!

Have been coming to this bar for a few years now and love both the bar and the sit down area. They have the best mac and cheese I've ever had and their chicken fingers are delicious! You always receive great service no matter what part of the bar you're at. And we love Chris!! He's the best bartender there! Everyone is awesome though! Definitely a must do in Park Slope.
Great local joint with great food and beer. Never disappoints.
Love it
Nice place. Good beers and good food.

I went here to buy some food, mainly. First, the food is really tasty. I had a Bison burger here. It was a big plate that was very filling and had plenty of vegetables. The two people I came with ordered fish and something chicken related. They were both happy. I can also say the beer is great (most of which is craft or craft-like). Best of all, the human factor is superb. I really liked the bartender. He has a great personality and is very chill. I think his name is Chris (?). Anyway, I recommend this place if you are looking for bar food and for a great selection of beers. I'd say the beer selection is even better than some of the local bars around here. All in all, great experience!
Amazing place. Great drinks. Food was good. Staff were courteous.
I always enjoy their food. It has a nice and cozy atmosphere. The staff is friendly and helpful.
Great go to. Really amazing food, I always trust the specials. Great balance of food, sports, drinking and a nice backyard. Come say hi.
EVERYTHING was amazing! Such big portions. So so delicious. Diego was so sweet!

Atmosphere was cozy. Came with my niece and the waiter Ricky was very nice and friendly. I had a burger which was nice and juicy. She had the mac and cheese with bacon bits. As good as the burger was it paled in comparison to the mac n cheese. One of the best I've ever tasted. Definitely worth it. Will come again even if it's only for the mac n cheese.
Nice place. But we got noisy neighbors on next table.
Excellent food,  especially the kale salad with chicken and great beer options for happy hour.  Very reasonably priced!
Perfect place . Full of entertainment . Perfect lighting . Delicious Food at reasonable prices
Top notch service, food, and drinks.

One of the best bars and restaurants in Brooklyn. It feels like an upscale Irish pub with Irish/American comfort food. The bar serves both high-end cocktails and cheap beer. Great and friendly staff, rarely a loud set of customers at the bar. Very eclectic playlist, but always playing great music. Stop by and realize you don't want to be anywhere else.
We always go there after our softball games and they always have room to accommodate us.  Great beer selection and delicious food!
Great food. Rsnbl price. Nice ambiance . Variety of dishes
Love this place. Always consistent. Friendly staff and owner. Great beers on tap. Best Guinness around. Also great food.
Good was great service was alright
They must have truffle oil on their fries or something, completely unlisted on their menu, I was sick for nearly a week after eating there.
Decent brunch menu. Decent beer list.

Waiter was very nice and attentive but for the second time burgers are medium well/well when ordered med rare and medium, specifically pink.  Also bun was so stale.  We did not complain and I am confident they would have tried to make it right but hard for us with our toddler and newborn.  The fries are amazing and $5 beer and wine on weekend can't be beat!
Great local spot, good and affordable food and drinks list, and the bartenders are friendly and fun.
Wonderful food,cosy atmosphere and the place also has a backyard .Had a wonderful time!
Great happy hour deals. Nice size portions on the meals. Attentive service.
Good service

Decent bar/restaurant. I ordered the seared tuna with cauliflower which was OK. While it was seared, it also needed to be cooked through, which makes me slightly question the quality of the fish, but overall the dish was OK. Price wasn't crazy. Tap list was nice.
You must try the buffalo burger.
Tottenham v. Liverpool Championship finala
Great service, friendly staff and delicious food reasonably priced.
Ricky is a great server and the food is so good
Excellent food and service!  Even better beer🍺
Good food and excellent service
Love the Food, Love the Vibe, Love this place. All thats missing is sweet potatoe fries and onion rings.
Great food at a reasonable price!

Good food, good choices in beer with some deliciousness from Germany available, good prices, combined with solid customer service makes this place a win.  If you have a kid, especially a newborn or older this is the place for you. Every bathroom has proper changing stations and very clean.  I love coming here and there's also a bar for the adults not looking for a table or on a single day out. Good atmosphere for a date (first date maybe).
Wings and Steak sandwich was excellent. The owner John is a gentleman and bought us some after dinner drinks. Great selection of beers on tap to choose from.

A pretty nice and cozy place to just sit and relax. Food is good also. Got the Blackened Catfish which was tasty. The Jalapeno Margarita was banging. My server Ricky and the rest of the staff was very friendly. I will definitely come again....
The bartenders are super nice! Their mac is great too. Low lighting but it's cozy. Good for extroverts because almost everyone is nice lol
Servers are nice. Brunch is on par with the neighborhood, meaning fine but not great. Dark inside but comfortable decor.
It was a really good spot! I wish they kept some of the specials they do weekly as part of the permanent menu but still amazing! Definitely get the Mac and cheese!
The food is good and the atmosphere is great as well. The only thing I'd caution is that on Sunday the kitchen closes from 4pm till after 5 for dinner.
Garbage service at the bar. Took us fifteen minutes to get served at 12:20am. Also, two local beers in BROOKLYN?
excellent 50¢ wings Sunday and Monday
Great breakfast burrito. Other good is usually pretty good.
Good casual night life, dim atmosphere.
Love their food, both dinner and brunch are great and are very reasonably priced. Good beer and wine selection. Incredibly friendly staff.
Been looking for a place to drink and eat whilst watching NFL. Great bar, excellent wings and super bar peeps
Great food. Lively atmosphere
Poached eggs came out hard boiled, bloody mary left an aweful taste and server was ignoring our table

Excellent craft beer menu. I had a Köstritzer. My picture is a little misleading as this menu item is listed with bacon a d sausage however they had a substitution listed for salmon making this pescetarian very happy. Relaxed atmosphere with bar and restaurant style seating.
Favorite place to hang with friends and order a bunch of appetizers and drinks.  Staff is so friendly  and attentive even though we usually  stay for a long time
great atmosphere, great wide selections of beers and good happy hour specials. Bartenders are amazing!, love this place
Good food and ambiance
nice neighborhood restaurant.  Good chili and burgers.
Always a great spot. Almost all dishes I have had have been awesome. You can never go wrong. And plus their beer on tap is of good quality. My favorite Reeisdorf Kolchs, pairs great with any meal.
Go to spot in South Slope. Awesome bartenders and great new wing special and Sunday and Monday!
Place serve too quality dishes...drinks are fine bit the service was outstanding...especially our server Ricky.  He ensured our satisfaction.
So nice and has a big yard out back .
Natasha and the manager know how to serve guests.
Their chicken finger appetizer is not your typical chicken finger.  It's not deep fried and is lightly breaded. Only issue is that the breading was falling off the meat.

Pretty much my favorite bar in the area, fast service, attentive bartenders, and a good atmosphere make it a perfect place to have a beer after work or stop in for dinner. The drink selection will ensure anyone can find something they like. When it comes to the food you can throw a dart at the menu and never walk away unsatisfied.
Everytime I've eaten, everything I've tried has been exceptional!
Wait staff very fun, steak sandwich a bit tough
Really good burger. Good selection of beers. Friendly staff.
Ricky is the best
Decent drinks and great food.
Very good bartenders,  excellent drinks,  good food
Great atmosphere. Had the Mac and cheese it was delicious
Great neighborhood joint
Love this place.
Great food, drinks and nieghbor hood folks.
Great food great atmosphere it was my first time there but I plan to come again
Great mac & cheese
Great Beer Selection,  and good food too !!
Solid.
Friendly staff, great burger
Nice comfy spot bloody Mary with bacon was delicious burgers are good cheap drinks would return

We were part of a large group reservation that filled the entire back room.  The servers were attentive and the food was excellent. Worth noting are the chicken fingers, sliders, and Mac and cheese.  Will be coming back to try out their full menu.
Great mustard with pretzel. Good beers
OMG the food is very good here. Burgers is the best 👍👍👍. I have been coming here for many years and it is always nice atmosphere,  great service and tasty. Love the places.

What can I say after moving out of town and then coming back to our go to place for a baby shower and they knock it out of the ballpark. The service and the food spot on. The burgers, wraps, portobello mushrooms, Mac & cheese. All I can say is go, go. Have next family party. Enjoy enjoy
One of the best bars in the city
Great food and service. Neighborhood go to.
Great brunch. A comfortable  first date spot. We were able to talk and get to know each other. The waitress was attentive, friendly, and allowed us to take our time.
comfortable setting and quiet bar with a decent variety of beer selections. food is good.
Excellent food.. Great bartenders.
Food is fabulous, drinks are great and  bartenders are favorites!
Came here for NYE looking for a place to sit with friends. We got dinner and it was very tasty!!
They have an amazing and friendly bar tender named Chris. We loved the music selection. The venue has lots of TV's so it's a good place to watch a game.
Amazing food and great blood mary's
Great atmosphere, excellent food, very reasonable prices, and the staff is wonderful!

I came here for brunch on a weekend with 2 friends. I tried their duck hash and it was very good. Prices are extremely reasonable for brunch. My friend found an egg shell piece in her eggs benedict unfortunately. I would come here again, but try their burgers or bar food instead of brunch.

Is your regular pub with nice drinks and good food.  Wife and I were in the area looking for lunch on a Sunday. Found this place and we're offered the brunch menu. Pretty standard. She asked for the burger I had the steak and eggs. Food was pretty good. The coffee was surprisingly delicious, especially for a pub. The beer selection was pretty decent.  As we were eating we started getting these really foul smells. First I thought it was the dude on the table next to us farting. But when it kept coming I thought it was impossible for anyone to fart that much so I asked the waitress about the smell (thinking the restroom had a leak... or maybe a gas leak from the kitchen??) But she said it was one of their cheeses.... A Gouda or something like that... So, beware of the fart-like smelling cheese. The world we live in.
Nice laid back bar restaurant.  Pretty decent fish and chips.  Can be loud on weekends.
Good ciders on tap, friendly staff, good fries
Good food and drinks
Great atmosphere, good music, good food and good drinks. Staff is friendly. I recommend the blue cheese burger
Nice menu and specials. Good beer selections on tap. Quite noisy on a Friday night. Service was great and the food was good.
Great service and food!
Great friendly bar. Solid casual America food in a nice atmosphere.
Spectacular brunch
A great place for a quiet drink. Good food and good bar staff.
Fries are really good. Service is lacking.
the brussle sprouts and steak sandwich are to die for, cant wait to go back!
Awesome food, great atmosphere with lots of space, huge awesome back patio
Food and service is great! Excellent bar to watch the game.

Great local bar. All day I dreamed about good steak and finally I had it. My husband took their classic burger, turned out it goes with craft beer 👌everything was perfect - food, portions and service.
Stephanie was great and so was the food.
Go here and get chicken pot pie! It is literally the best.

Came here for a late brunch on a Saturday and it was basically empty which meant that service was good! I had the French toast and it was delicious!! Great portion of food for the price.  Definitely a solid place.
Great food and great drinks but service can be slow at times.
Excellent food and service

I love this place. Great neighborhood bar. Food is usually an 8-9 out of 10. Could be less, depending on what you order. Good beer selection. I would prefer more beer turnover, but I really like hanging here. Great, friendly bartenders.
Great food. Awesome happy hour specials. Excellent service.

The waiter forgot to take our order after we were seated. The Mediterranean salad special was good, but the waiter forgot I ordered chicken with it. Cool vibe and atmosphere, but not the best service.
I enjoyed their chili, and they have a great atmosphere.
Great food!
Great vibe, consistent and delicious bar food, and an excellent selection of taps. The cocktails are decent, and the bartenders are friendly and genuinely hospitable.

Really enjoyed the meat and cheese plate and trying all the various combinations.   Had a tasty bison burger.  Server was very knowledgeable about the menu items and suggested many of the items we tried for dinner.

Friendly staff, though I only sit at the bar, everyone is very nice. They started doing movies Sunday nights. They set it up on the projector in the back and one of the front tvs too. Food is tasty and if you are at the bar ask for the  burger and beer special (burger and fries with a free beer)
Awesome place for food and drinks, atmosphere is amazing
Good happy hour. Good food.
Good food, spacious bar, and for some reason never that crowded when I go
Great food!! And the drinks are awesome.
I have a speech impediment, and the woman answering the phone was flat out rude because she couldn't understand me, and hung up.
I have only had brunch here. The food is good, but the cocktails are the real reason to stop by. The Greyhound is part of the brunch special at only $4.00; and they use real  grapefruit juice.
Great beer selection and brunch. do it

This is hands down one of the best kept secrets in this neighborhood.  I travel to NYC usually once a month to visit and we eat here usually twice per weekend visit. You need to try this restaurant!!!!
Waitstaff was not pushy or overbearing. Great spot for drinks, and good pub food.
Really great homemade fries and solid draft beer selection.

This place is lovely. Great bar, plus it has a lovely outdoor area. The staff are so friendly and attentive. I love that there is real Irish people who know how to treat customers. So attentive without being annoying. Great drink service too. They have lovely cocktails. The food is great too. I love the eggs Benedict and the burger is great.

Interesting cocktail menu and the bartender is willing to accommodate tweaks (like removing agave from a cocktail to reduce sweetness). The servers are fast and reliable, quickly replacing empty water bottles, bringing the next round and serving up brunch. Huge interior with a bi-level outdoor space that is just lovely. Great for brunch or just drinks. Note: Not dog-friendly as they serve food on the patio.

I think this will be my new local pub. Its near my flat. It has a beer garden. It serves drip coffee which is ... as much as drip coffee can be ... drinkable. It has a great range of feed and drinks and a cozy atmosphere.  Yep, I hope they are proud to be called my Local.
